      <div class="mume markdown-preview   ">
271
      <h1 class="mume-header" id="4-requirements">4. Requirements</h1>
272

273
<h2 class="mume-header" id="principles">Principles</h2>
274

275
<ul>
276
<li>WoT architecture should enable mutual interworking of different eco-systems using web technology.</li>
277
<li>WoT architecture should be based on the web architecture using RESTful APIs.</li>
278
<li>WoT architecture should allow to use multiple payload formats which are commonly used in the web.</li>
279
</ul>
280
<h2 class="mume-header" id="thing-functionalities">Thing functionalities</h2>
281

282
<ul>
283
<li>WoT architecture should allow thing&apos;s to have functionalities such as
284
<ul>
285
<li>reading thing&apos;s status information</li>
286
<li>updating thing&apos;s status information which might cause actuation</li>
287
<li>subscribing to, receiving and unsubscribing to the notification of the change of thing&apos;s status information.</li>
288
<li>invoking functions with input and output parameters which would cause certain actuation or calculation.</li>
289
<li>subscribing to, receiving and unsubscribing to the notification which does not directly relate to thing&apos;s status information.</li>
290
</ul>
291
</li>
292
</ul>
293
<h2 class="mume-header" id="search-and-discovery">Search and discovery</h2>
294

295
<ul>
296
<li>WoT architecture should allow clients to know thing&apos;s attributes, functionalities and their access points, prior to access to the thing itself.</li>
297
<li>WoT architecture should allow clients to search things by its attributes and functionalities.</li>
298
<li>WoT architecture should allow semantic search of its functionalities based on unified vocabulary, regardless of naming of its functionalities.</li>
299
</ul>
300
<h2 class="mume-header" id="description-mechanism">Description mechanism</h2>
301

302
<ul>
303
<li>WoT architecture should support common description mechanism which enables describing things and their functions.</li>
304
<li>Such description should be not only human-readable, but also machine-readable.</li>
305
<li>Such description should allow semantic annotation of its structure and described contents.</li>
306
<li>Such description should be able to be exchanged using multiple formats which are commonly used in the web.</li>
307
</ul>
308
<h2 class="mume-header" id="description-of-attributes">Description of attributes</h2>
309

310
<ul>
311
<li>WoT architecture should allow describing thing&apos;s attributes such as
312
<ul>
313
<li>name</li>
314
<li>explanation</li>
315
<li>version of spec, format and description itself</li>
316
<li>links to other related things and information</li>
317
</ul>
318
</li>
319
<li>Such description should support internationalization.</li>
320
</ul>
321
<h2 class="mume-header" id="description-of-functionalities">Description of functionalities</h2>
322

323
<ul>
324
<li>WoT architecture should allow describing thing&apos;s functionalities which is shown in ## Thing functionalities</li>
325
</ul>
326
<h2 class="mume-header" id="network">Network</h2>
327

328
<ul>
329
<li>WoT architecture should support multiple web protocols which are commonly used.</li>
330
<li>Such protocols include 1)protocols commonly used in the internet and 2)protocols commonly used in the local area network</li>
331
<li>WoT architecture should allow using multiple web protocols to access to the same functionality.</li>
332
<li>WoT architecture should allow using mixture of multiple protocols to the functionalities of the same thing (e.g. HTTP and WebSocket).</li>
333
</ul>
334
<h2 class="mume-header" id="deployment">Deployment</h2>
335

336
<ul>
337
<li>WoT architecture should support wide variety of thing capability such as edge devices with resource restrictions and virtual things on the cloud, based on the same model.</li>
338
<li>WoT architecture should support multiple levels of thing hierarchy with intermediate entities such as gateways and proxies.</li>
339
<li>WoT architecture should support accessing things in the local network from the outside of the local network (the internet or other local network), considering network address translation.</li>
340
</ul>
341
<h2 class="mume-header" id="application">Application</h2>
342

343
<ul>
344
<li>WoT architecture should allow describing applications on the wide variety of things such as edge device, gateway, cloud and UI/UX device, using web standard technology based on the same model.</li>
345
</ul>
346
<h2 class="mume-header" id="legacy-adaption">Legacy adaption</h2>
347

348
<ul>
349
<li>WoT architecture should allow mapping of legacy IP and non-IP protocols to web protocols, supporting wide variety of hierarchy, where such legacy protocols are terminated and translated.</li>
350
<li>WoT architecture should allow transparent use of existing IP protocols without translation, which follow RESTful architecture.</li>
351
</ul>
352
<h2 class="mume-header" id="security">Security</h2>
353

354
<ul>
355
<li>WoT architecture should support multiple security mechanism commonly used in the web, such as Basic, Digest, Bearer and OAuth2.0.</li>
356
</ul>
357

358
      </div>
